    old "The forest gives way to rocks and green hills, but among the tall trees are numerous monkeys, sitting in small groups, loud, yet shorter than half your size. They distort the green leaves with red, brown, white, and blue fur. \n\nAs you approach their territory, their excitement grows. They climb up and down the trunks, sway on vines, jump between branches, or hang down, putting to use their long tails. They throw at you countless angry glances and grunts, but also cones, branches, and chestnuts. \n\nA piece of their fresh feces lands close to {color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color}, but the pack’s aim is rather miserable. "
