    # game/areas/shortcut.rpy:666
    old "You grab your [custom1] head toward the crag slowly. Climbing to the top is simple enough. You step forward and take a few swings, raising your voice in your taunts. \n\nThe beasts keep running left and right, stretching out their shells, jumping up, and warning you with their shrieks. They are quick, nimble, and as loud as a bird. \n\nFinally, the largest kobold, whose head is covered with red scales, risks an attack. It gets close enough to take a hit in the maw, and while its nearest companions follow its lead, the others hesitate. One of them manages to reach your sleeve, tearing it as you lift it up, but you then grab it and throw it away, right into another member of its pack. \n\nAfter that, the entire group runs to the rock face, and makes impressive jumps onto the higher ledges, leaving you with a few more discontent screeches. You doubt it’s the first time their prey gets stolen. "
