    # game/areas/shortcut.rpy:774
    old "The tall trees cover you with the shadows. You’re forced to get on your boots to move beneath a few of the fallen boughs. Soon, you reach a few shrubs at the edge of the fighting ground, and tether your mount nearby. \n\nYou count six birds spread around the dry glade. They’re as tall as your palfrey, with pointy, curved beaks and tiny wings. Their feathers are green, blue, and white. \n\nThe saurian, surrounded by the predators, looks like it could break their necks with just a breath. It matches your height, but it’s as wide as it is tall, and as long as a house, even without its long tail. It’s covered with firm plates, aligned in horizontal rows down the entire shell, and its head resembles a horned helmet. On its sides are two rows of irregular spikes, each of them longer than your forearm. The creature swings its tail left and right, scaring off the runners with the massive “club” at its end. "
