    # game/areas/shortcut.rpy:834
    old "With the axe in your hand, you jump out of the shrubs and stride toward the dragon. The surprised runner “bows” to you, raising its voice, but seeing how you keep your distances, it just shakes its colorful head and moves away. \n\nThe saurian pays close attention to your approach, not sure what’s going on. During this moment of hesitation, a member of the flock gets close enough to peck the monster’s head. The terrified creature starts turning around. \n\nThe loud steps cover up the shout of the trampled dragonling, to the birds’ joyful screech. The dragon tries one last attack, furiously moving backwards after one of the runners. It takes a wide swing with its tail, but the club hits only the trunk of the nearest tree. \n\nThe plant starts to crack, like a tower hit by lightning. The earth trembles, and as you look at {color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color}, it panically pulls the rope, trying to set itself free. "
