    old "The tree crowns once again block the sunlight. You enter another corridor of fallen boughs, and the more curvy the path gets, the quicker the beast shortens the gap between you. \n\nYou make another turn and almost pull on the reins at the sight of another beast. Its limbs, as thick as tree trunks, are taller than {color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color}, and are around the road, not on it. The beast’s tower-like neck is devouring the leaves, chewing both loudly and slowly. By its long tail, now leaning on the ground, there’s a trail of broken plants and moved soil. The beast’s skin is bumpy, parts of it are brown, green, red... \n\nYou now realize that your pursuer has also slowed down. For now, the giant ignores your presence - if it even sees you, next to it you’re like a fly. You can’t ride around the dragon, and you can’t turn back. "
